# Playground responsive layout

When editing **`field-demo/projects/playground/`** layout or global shell styles, keep this pattern unless the user requests a different design.

## Wide viewports

- **Viewport shell** — `html`, `body`, and `app-root` fill the height; **`body` uses `overflow: hidden`** so the document does not scroll as a single page.
- **Two columns** — Preview (field demo) on the left with **flex growth**; **Controls** on the right at a **fixed width**. Each column scrolls on its own: **`overflow-y: auto`**, **`min-height: 0`** (flex children), and **`overscroll-behavior: contain`** so wheel/touch on one side does not move the other.

## Narrow viewports (mobile / small tablet)

- **Breakpoint** — **`max-width: 900px`** (adjust in SCSS and in any TypeScript that references the same value, e.g. `resize` handlers, so they stay in sync).
- **Controls** — Not in normal document flow; **fixed** off-screen to the right, **slide in** when open. **`pointer-events: none`** when closed so hidden controls are not focusable.
- **Menu control** — **Fixed top-right** button toggles the drawer; icon may switch to close when open. Use **`env(safe-area-inset-*)`** for notched devices.
- **Dismiss** — **Backdrop** click, second tap on the menu control, **`Escape`**, and **window resize wider than the breakpoint** should close the drawer.
- **Viewport meta** — Playground **`index.html`** should keep **`viewport-fit=cover`** when tuning safe-area behavior.

If you change the breakpoint or shell behavior, update **stylesheet(s) and TS together** where both apply.
